Answer:
gpt_response: The SMILES expression of (3R)-1-(2H-tetrazol-5-yl)pyrrolidin-3-ol is as follows: C1CC(O)(CN1)N2C=NNN2. This SMILES notation represents the molecular structure of the specified compound in a concise and standardized format for computational purposes in chemical informatics. The designation of chirality at the 3rd carbon atom corresponds to the (3R) configuration, indicating the three-dimensional spatial arrangement of substituent groups in relation to the tetrazole and pyrrolidine moieties. The use of SMILES notation facilitates the communication and manipulation of chemical structures with precision and efficiency within the scientific community.
